<br>
I have tried to be clear and concise, while representing most points of view as fairly as possible.<br>
<br>
Please feedback in this thread.<br>
<br>
A similar summary of reactions to the new Planar abilities will be prepared in the next few days.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Razamtazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Abuser of EZCodes</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalanzsonofanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A> at: 10/1/02 3:56:28 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalanzsonofanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 1917<br> <font color=#333333>(9/26/02 4:55:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Proposed Summary of Pop Spell Reactions</span><hr size=1> Pre-PoP Reaction Summary<br>
<br>
The release of various text and data files to test has allow mages outside the beta-test of PoP a preliminary chance to evaluate the new spells and abilities.  The purpose of this document is to summarize the various reactions, suggested alternatives, and critiques that have been seen in this and other forums.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> OverView:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
While mages have never spoken with a single voice, there are several overlapping schools of thought with vocal adherents.  These include:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>       DPS Masters</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> believe that mages are and should be almost exclusively about about dealing damage.  Non-damage utility may be viewed with suspicion, as unwanted capabilities likely have a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>       &quot;cost&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> in DPS.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>       Nukers</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> are a sub-set of the DPS school which believes additionally that mages should be no worse than third best nukers, and really should be second after Wizards.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>       Pet Masters</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> are concerned that mage pets remain the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>       &quot;best,&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or at minimum that pets remain the defining feature of mages.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>       Epickers</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> are a sub-set of the Pet Master school who are concerned that the epic pet remain the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>       &quot;best of the best,&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or at minimum, not made obsolete by non-epic pets.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Pet Lovers</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> are another sub-set of Pet Masters who prefer to sustain a single pet, and dislike chaining pets.  Many epickers are naturally pet lovers.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>       Conservatives</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> are against new non-thematic capabilities, and would prefer strengthening existing capabilties.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>       Eclectics</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> are open to new capabalities, even if non-thematic.<br>
<br>
These are by no means exclusive.<br>
<br>
We will start with the reactions to the proposed new spell list, since that was released first.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  New Pets:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Everyone mostly happy, although no one can tell how good the pets are, or whether they can be summoned in non-PoP zones.  No one seems too upset by the non-standard ordering of the elements.  Epickers would be concerned if these new pets make the epic obsolete.<br>
<br>
The quality of these pets will likely make or break the value of the expansion for the majority of mages.  On the one hand, they must be good enough to deal with the new environment, on the other hand many epicked mages will be distressed if they make the epic obsolete.  Given that the new direct damage spells will likely not keep pace with the environment, mages are dependent on pets to do so.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  New Self Buffs:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Disappointed at lack of upgrade in <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Phantasmal Armor</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> series.  <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Strongly</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> suggest componentless upgrade to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>       Transon's Phantasmal Protection</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> New Summoned Focus Items:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Many mages would prefer than the existing focus items, summoned and dropped, be extended up to level 65 instead of adding another tier of focus items.  Some complain that summoned items should never be better than dropped loot.  Since initially, mages will be the only easy source of top tier focus items, many mages dread the burden of summoning them.<br>
<br>
The summoned bag of focus gear is flawed, as the mage will likely be wearing at least one summoned focus item, causing the bag summon to fail unless the mage drops or destroys all their focus items first.  This eliminates almost all the convenience of a summoned bag of focus gear.<br>
<br>
The addition of a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /drop</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> command to drop whatever item is on the cursor would be a big improvement.  Likewise, auto dropping any summoned lore item instead of having the summon fail would help immensely.  Alternately, remove the lore tag from focus gear.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Imbues:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Conservatives mistrust new non-thematic capability of unknown value.  Many are disappointed that this takes up half of our available level 65 spells, as it is non-mage specific.  These would leave only two <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>       &quot;real&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> 65th level spells: <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>       Call of the ArchMage</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, which is seen dubiously by Conservatives, and Sun Vortex.  From the conservative or DPSer point of view, this leaves only <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>one</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  &quot;real&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> mage spell, which is very disappointing.  Possible solution includes nice upgrade to phantasmal armor series here with minimal stacking issues.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Damage Spells:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  AOEers are disappointed at lack of new PBAE spell.  If <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>anyone</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> gets an PBAE damage spell in PoP, then wizards and mages should.  Nukers are concerned that mage relative nuking rank is in danger of being seriously degraded by other class's upgrades.  Note that there are two rains, of which <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>       Maelstrom of Thunder</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, with three waves of 800 damage for 800 mana, appears to suck so bad as to be unacceptable.  As the distinguishing practical feature of rains is their potential mana efficiency combined with rate of delivery, it seems impossible to justify <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  MoT</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> as currently listed.  Most would prefer some other damage spell at 64th level other than a rain, for example, a fast hard nuke upgrade to Char or Scars of Sigil.  Even an upgraded Damage over Time spell would be better than <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  MoT</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
It has also been noted that both new Druid Rains are better in all ways to the two new Mage rains.  Rains have always been a major damage line for mages, and never been more than a sideshow for Druids.  Nukers and other strongly suggest that the mage rains be improved.<br>
<br>
Specific opinions on exact statistics for the nukes are far too varied to summarize here, except to say many naturally want better damage to mana ratios and higher damage per second.  The direct nukes, Firebolt of Tallon, Black Steel, and Sun Vortex are probably close to their proper values, but should definitely not be seriously downgraded.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Mezz and Charm Summoned:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> are strongly opposed by DPSers and conservatives, who would rather have something more consistent with their vision of the Mage class.  A 2K anti-summoned nuke has been proposed as an alternative, but given <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>       Banishment</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>       Turn Summoned</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> might add little.  While a significant number of eclectic mages welcome the new spell line, others hate it with a passion.  There is concern about the utility of the spell, given the lack of summoned mobs, and if it useable in only one or two PoP zones, many will be disappointed.<br>
<br>
It has been pointed out that mages lack basic tools to cope with a broken charm.  Without stun, root, etc., and denied a pet, mages will have a hard time when charm breaks.  Mezz is not a sufficient answer, as mezzed creatures cannot be charmed.  The consequences of this should be examined when evaluating the practical utility of charm summoned.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>       Damage Shields:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Almost all mages are very disappointed at the lack of a single target damage shield upgrade.  The group spell, while okay, cannot be cast on pets, and likely conflicts with important melee buffs.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>       Malosinia:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> is pretty much as expected.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Missing Spells:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Pet Masters are disappointed to see no new pet heals, buffs or summons.  Pet Lovers are particularly concerned about the lack of a pet heal upgrade, and worry that the new environnment will be so brutal that chaining pets will be forced, effectively obsoleting the epic on the planes.  Some are disappointed at the lack of Monster Summoning 4 at level 65, others consider that spell line to be a joke.  As mentioned before, an upgrade to the phantasmal armor line seems to be missing.  There is not a single new summon, for which many mages are grateful.  Single target damage shield missing, as above.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>       SUMMARY OF SPELL REACTION:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  If the pets are good enough, and the nukes are good enough, most mages are likely to be fairly satisfied, with a few exceptions:<br>
<br>
1) Lack of TPP upgrade<br>
2) Lack of single target DS upgrade<br>
3) Lack of pet heal, buff or pet only item<br>
4) Shortage of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  &quot;real&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> mage spells at 65th level<br>
5) Those who oppose the new spell lines.<br>
6) Mage rains greatly inferior to druid rains<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    EDIT:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Added lack of pet heal, reordered exceptions.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    EDIT:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Mentioned unfavorable comparison of new mage and druid rain spells.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    EDIT:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Emphasized that pets will make or break the expansion for most mages.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   EDIT:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Add concerns that mages lack tools to cope with broken charms.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  EDIT:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Emphasized concern of Pet Lovers over lack of new heal and forced pet chaining.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> EDIT:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Added comments on new summoned focus gear.<br>
<br>
