I think the consensus about the 51-60 (non-epic) pets is that Air is usually the best all-round pet for most situations, especially against casting mobs. Those that believe that (like myself) generally welcome getting Air quite early. Water is great if he can get in backstab position, but that can be a burden on the main tank in an exp group. Earth is situational IMO, but has by far the most HP, and is most useful against mobs that won't flee and deal raw damage.<br>
<br>
My main concern is about the new Fire pet. Will it be like the pre-50 fire pets and have a massive DS and high offensive power, or will it be a joke of a pet like the post-50 pets?<br>
<br>
Another question is whether or not the 61+ pets will keep the same characteristics as the 51-60 pets. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utezron.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tezron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#333333>(9/27/02 7:54:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   list looks pretty good. </span><hr size=1> agree with the above poster about the fire pets tho. <br>
