<br>
For me, the most important issues are<br>
<br>
1) Situational usefulness of post-60 pets (i.e. that they are unique enough to all have uses, with no clear &quot;best&quot; pet)<br>
2) M/D ratios on nukes should not be surpassed by any non-Wizard (class roles should be consistent and clear)<br>
3) Some &quot;core&quot; class features seem very undone: DSs, rains, put buffs, etc<br>
4) Vs. Summoned Mez, and especially Charm would be nearly worthless in the current game.  Unless PoP is positively bursting with summoned creatures, these spells will be page 32 fodder.  Vs. Summoned Charm is especially dubious in value.  Even if these spells have value in PoP, they won't add much power to the Mage class, since the original game and all previous expansions are nearly devoid of summoned creatures, essentially limiting these spells to PoP-only.<br>
<br>
I think that pretty much sums up my thoughts. <p><CENTER>
