<br>
1. Pet power will make or break the expansion for mages.<br>
<br>
2. Conjuration based nukes that are upgrades to Scars and Char.  Fast casting but pack a punch.  Black Steel has the possibility if you drop the casting time to 5 sec.  Put a fire one in at level 64 that does say 1100 or 1150 damage with an equal casting time as the proposed black steel.<br>
<br>
3. Better ratio on rain spell (take it out for all I care) and reduce resist rate.  Would rather have upgrades to DD as proposed in #2 above than rain spells.<br>
<br>
4. Take out mez and charm.  We haven't done it for all our career we shouldn't now.<br>
<br>
5. Thanks for the new summoned items! (i.e. new bracers, earring...)  Would like to see at least one or two weapons for pets only that proc magic based and fire based damage.<br>
<br>
In conclusion most here believe we are a damage dealing class with minimal utility.  It is important that this is acknowledged and the class is progressed as such.  That means pets and nukes.  Those two things are what the people that play the class are looking for.<br>
